    "Dashboard design, business storytelling, and performance visualisation using Power BI.\n",
    "\n",
    "## Overview\n",
    "\n",
    "This project focuses on business dashboard development and visual communication using Power BI. It involved presenting business performance data in a way that is clear, interactive, and suitable for decision-making. The dashboard was designed to highlight key business indicators such as sales, costs, net profit, and category performance, while also making the information visually accessible for a wider audience.\n",
    "\n",
    "This project is important in my portfolio because it demonstrates my ability to move from raw business data toward organised visual insight. It also shows how data presentation plays a key role in helping people understand performance and identify patterns.\n",
    "\n",
    "## Dashboard Screens\n",
    "\n",
    "![](../images/powerbi-1.jpg){fig-alt=\"Power BI dashboard screen 1\"}\n",
    "![](../images/powerbi-2.jpg){fig-alt=\"Power BI dashboard screen 2\"}\n",
    "\n",
    "These dashboard screens show how business data can be summarised visually to support comparison, interpretation, and decision-making.\n",
    "\n",
    "## Method\n",
    "\n",
    "The dashboard was designed to summarise business performance across categories and support quick comparison of key measures. I focused on selecting the most meaningful indicators, organising them into a clear layout, and presenting trends in a visually readable way. This process strengthened my understanding of how dashboard structure affects interpretation.\n",
    "\n",
    "## Python Example\n",
    "\n",
    "The Python example below demonstrates a simple category-level comparison that supports dashboard interpretation and business reporting."
